<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-556-639  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 556 639.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Feb 26 1990 v7 n8 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Relational databases ported to VMS; Ultrix port planned. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tektron Software (product introduction).andO;Product:   Aspen/2 (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionRelational DBMSSoftware.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Relational database ported to VMS; Ultrix port plannedandM;LAKEWOOD, Colo.andP;  -- Tektron Software has ported its Aspen/2 relationaldatabase package to VMS and will port the software to Ultrix within the next90 days, company officials said.andM;Previously available for Unix, MS-DOS, OS/2 and Bull systems, Aspen/2requires no central database administration and uses English-like commandsfor developing applications, company officials said.andM;&quot;If users need to add new data elements or fields to an existing datastructure, they can do so themselves without [the help of] databaseadministrators,&quot; said Richard Barkey, president of Keystep, the Lakewood,Colo.-based distributor of Aspen/2.andM;Aspen has a simple command to define an element, said Tektron President DanHegarty.andP;  If users are able to write to a file, then Aspen/2 will record thenew element as being in the next file.andP;  Columns and rows can be added tocontain data or not, depending how a user sets them up, Hegarty said.andM;&quot;The software also provides a simple method for linking databases,&quot; Barkeysaid.andP;  &quot;The Link Database command [can be] done via a user macro.andP;  And themacros can be stored in the Aspen database.&quot;andM;Aspen/2 supports full-screen data entry, creation of application menus, easyad hoc queries, formatted reports, and data import and export capabilities.andM;Data fields in the Aspen/2 database can be used for direct search and datasequencing without the use of external indexes.andM;As many as 100 databases can be linked logically on common fields, and datafields can be added or removed from a database at any time withoutreorganizing the database, company officials said.andM;Tektron is currently considering adding support for SQL, according to Barkey.andM;Further information can be obtained from Keystep Corp., Tektron'sdistributor, at 7580 W. 16th St., Lakewood, CO 80215, (800) 828-1484; (303)238-7710.andO;</TEXT></DOC>